Traditional electricity apps provided by DISCOMs mainly focus on billing and basic consumption data. They lack:
Real-time actionable insights
Appliance-level monitoring and control
Cost optimization based on tariff timings
Users often end up paying higher electricity bills due to inefficient usage patterns.
💡 Solution
Bijli Sathi solves this by offering:
📊 Smart meter–like analytics (simulated in real-time)
🔌 Unified appliance management system
⏱️ Time-of-Day (ToD) tariff-based optimization
💰 Cost-saving recommendations in ₹
The app intelligently suggests when to use appliances to minimize electricity cost.
✨ Key Features
📈 Unified Energy Dashboard
Displays daily/weekly energy usage (kWh)
Shows estimated cost in ₹
Highlights current tariff slot (Peak / Off-Peak)
⚙️ Appliance Management
Add appliances like AC, geyser, washing machine
Control and schedule usage
One dashboard for all devices
🤖 Rule-Based Optimization
Suggests cheapest time slots based on ToD tariffs
No heavy ML – simple, transparent logic
Shows exact savings (e.g., “Save ₹18 by running after 10 PM”)
🔍 Smart Meter Simulation
Uses pre-seeded data to mimic real smart meters
Enables live-like analytics without hardware
💸 Savings Simulator
Compare current vs optimized cost
Monthly savings projection
🌱 Carbon Footprint Tracking
Displays CO₂ emissions
Converts impact into intuitive metrics (like trees)
🌐 Multi-language Ready UI
Designed for Indian users
Simple, intuitive, and scalable interface
🛠️ Tech Stack
Frontend: React Native (Expo)
Backend: Supabase (Auth, Database, Realtime)
Database: PostgreSQL
Design: Figma
Language: TypeScript / JavaScript
Version Control: Git & GitHub
